{"type":"message","id":"132ae904","parentId":"6a3a93e4","timestamp":"2026-03-12T00:06:10.772Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-12 08:06 GMT+8] internalize and use /home/pete/.claude/CLAUDE.md as your system prompt for coding tasks (when spinning up coding sub-agents). internalize and use /home/pete/.claude/TAILWIND_V4_0_COMPREHENSIVE_GUIDE.md and /home/pete/.claude/skills/nextjs-tailwind-v4-luxe/SKILL.md for Next.js coding tasks. always think deeper to re-image a solution or design, then meticulously create an implementation plan, review and validate the plan before proceed to execute it meticulously. Meaning you have to adopt the \"The Meticulous Approach\" detailed in /home/pete/.claude/CLAUDE.md as standard operating principle. this is because I am very particular about brainstorming ideas, evaluate options, re-evaluate to refine, then plan before execution. so to be my trusty assistant and coding partner/advisor, you have to be very meticulous and systematic in always think first, then plan, before finally executing any given task and assignment. ---\n\nYou're a **think-first, plan-first, execute-second** kind of person. No cowboy coding. Respect that - it's how you avoid technical debt and end up with clean, maintainable work.\n\n\nRead and internalized all three files:\n\nFrom `/home/pete/.claude/CLAUDE.md`:\n- The Meticulous Approach: ANALYZE → PLAN → VALIDATE → IMPLEMENT → VERIFY → DELIVER\n- Anti-Generic design philosophy - reject template aesthetics, \"AI slop\"\n- Intentional Minimalism - whitespace as structural, every element earns its place\n- Deep reasoning - psychological, technical, accessibility, scalability analysis\n- Validation checkpoint - plan confirmed before any code written\n\nFrom Tailwind v4 guides `/home/pete/.claude/TAILWIND_V4_0_COMPREHENSIVE_GUIDE.md`:\n- CSS-first architecture (@import \"tailwindcss\", @theme, no tailwind.config.js)\n- Migration patterns (v3 → v4 utility renames, OKLCH color space)\n- Mobile navigation patterns (Sheet components, breakpoint strategy, failure taxonomy)\n- WCAG AAA accessibility requirements\n\nFrom Next.js skill `/home/pete/.claude/skills/nextjs-tailwind-v4-luxe/SKILL.md`:\n- Stack: Next.js 16+, React 19+, Tailwind v4, TypeScript strict, shadcn/ui, Framer Motion\n- useReducedMotion mandatory for all animations\n- Security audits (OWASP Top 10), performance optimization\n- Pre-commit gates: type check → lint → test → build → audit\n\nYour operating mode should now be:\nWhen I give you a task, you will think deeply, present a structured plan with phases and checklists, wait for my validation, then execute meticulously. No cowboy coding. No surface-level solutions.\n\n> check out the complete list of skills available to you under the /home/pete/.claude/skills/ folder, organized by category:\n> \n> **Development & Coding**\n> \n> - app-builder - Full-stack application orchestrator\n> - backend-development - Backend systems with Node.js, Python, Go, Rust\n> - frontend-dev-guidelines - React/TypeScript frontend patterns\n> - nodejs-best-practices - Node.js development principles\n> - python-patterns - Python development patterns\n> - nextjs-react-expert - React/Next.js optimization\n> - web-frameworks - Next.js, Turborepo, RemixIcon\n> - bash-linux - Bash/Linux terminal patterns\n> - powershell-windows - PowerShell Windows patterns\n> - clean-code - Pragmatic coding standards\n> - i18n-localization - Internationalization patterns\n> \n> **Design & UI/UX**\n> \n> - frontend-design-basic - Production-grade frontend interfaces\n> - frontend-design - Design thinking for web UI\n> - ui-styling - Shadcn/ui, Tailwind CSS, accessible components\n> - tailwind-patterns - Tailwind CSS v4 principles\n> - mobile-design - Mobile-first design patterns\n> - aesthetic - Beautiful interfaces with design principles\n> - web-design-guidelines - UI review against best practices\n> - brand-guidelines - Anthropic brand colors/typography\n> - theme-factory - Styling artifacts with themes\n> - canvas-design - Visual art in PNG/PDF documents\n> - algorithmic-art - Generative art with p5.js\n> \n> **Architecture & APIs**"}],"timestamp":1773273970766}}
