{"type":"message","id":"6c809aba","parentId":"99a08070","timestamp":"2026-03-12T01:04:22.066Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user wants me to:\n1. Review the TrustSkill SKILL.md (which I already read above)\n2. Remember this protocol for scanning new skills before adding them to inventory\n3. Record this in long-term memory (MEMORY.md)\n\nLet me review what I found in the TrustSkill SKILL.md and then update MEMORY.md to include this security protocol as a core operational requirement.\n\nFrom my earlier read, the key points are:\n- TrustSkill v3.1 is an advanced security scanner for OpenClaw skills\n- It detects malicious code, hardcoded secrets, vulnerable dependencies, tainted data flows, backdoors, credential theft, etc.\n- 99% false positive reduction with NPM integrity hash whitelisting\n- Three scanning modes: fast, standard, deep\n- Must be run BEFORE installing any new skill from unknown sources\n- Location: /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/trustskill/\n- Prerequisites: source /opt/venv/bin/activate\n\nI need to update MEMORY.md to reflect this as a mandatory","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" I've already reviewed the TrustSkill SKILL.md. Let me update MEMORY.md to codify this as a **mandatory security"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773277409867}}
