{"type":"message","id":"af8e60e9","parentId":"da4d0a9e","timestamp":"2026-03-12T15:57:17.913Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user has asked me to categorize all the skills under the main `/home/pete/.claude/skills/` folder. He wants me to read their headers and save the list in my inventory for future reference.\n\nThere are about 100 skill directories. I need to read the SKILL.md files from each and extract their YAML headers. This is going to be a lot of tool calls. I should be strategic about this.\n\nLet me first get a list of all the skill directories without the dots and special files, then read their YAML headers.\n\nI'll need to:\n1. Get the list of directories\n2. Read SKILL.md from each directory\n3. Extract the YAML header\n4. Categorize them\n5. Save to MEMORY.md\n\nLet me start by listing the directories and then reading the SKILL.md files in batches. I should be careful about rate limits and token usage. Let me","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" I'll systematically extract YAML headers from all skill directories and categorize them. This is a substantial task — let me work"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773330884959}}
